The name MUST fit the local terrain ({node_biome}) — do not name a desert location after frost, or a snowy peak after jungle.

Example (crossroads in a dark forest region):
{{"name": "Gallows' Crossing", "label_description": "A bleak, windswept intersection of two ancient roads deep in the Thornweald, where the elves hang warning totems from the gnarled oaks."}}

Example (settlement in a pastoral region):
{{"name": "Goldmere", "label_description": "A prosperous market town nestled in the golden wheat fields of the Sunlit Marches, its inns overflowing with adventurers bound for the nearby barrow-mounds."}}

Generate a unique, fitting name for this {node_type} and a short one-line description (label_description).
Output ONLY valid JSON: {{"name": "...", "label_description": "..."}}

